<p>Tampa's hot-humid climate demands high-efficiency HVAC systems with excellent dehumidification capabilities. The ideal HVAC system for Tampa homes should have a minimum SEER rating of 16, though SEER 18-20 systems provide optimal efficiency for the region's long cooling seasons that can extend from March through November. Heat pumps are particularly well-suited for Tampa because they provide both heating and cooling efficiently, taking advantage of the mild winter temperatures that rarely drop below 40¬∞F.</p>

