<p>Tampa Electric offers various rebate programs for energy-efficient upgrades. Their residential energy efficiency rebate program provides up to \$1,600 for qualifying HVAC systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher. Heat pump water heaters can qualify for rebates up to \$500, and smart thermostats receive rebates of \$50-75. While Tampa Electric doesn't currently offer direct solar rebates, they do provide net metering, allowing solar customers to receive credit for excess electricity production at the full retail rate of 11.8¬¢ per kWh. Property tax exemptions for solar installations mean the added home value from solar panels won't increase property tax assessments.</p>

