<p>South Tampa neighborhoods like Palma Ceia and Beach Park offer excellent solar potential with many homes having optimal south-facing roof exposure, though proximity to Tampa Bay can create additional humidity challenges requiring robust HVAC dehumidification. The downtown Channel District and Harbour Island feature many high-rise condos where individual solar installations aren't feasible, but community solar programs through Tampa Electric may provide alternatives. East Tampa and Seminole Heights neighborhoods often feature older homes that can benefit significantly from both solar and HVAC upgrades, with the potential for substantial energy bill reductions due to less efficient existing systems.</p>

